   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>TRUTH LESSONS LEVEL THREE</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE TYPES IN THE OLD TESTAMENT LESSON SIX SARAH AND HAGAR OUTLINE Sarah symbolizing the covenant of God s promise: God s promise being fulfilled by God s grace for those who inherit the promise.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Not by the energy of man s flesh.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Only those who are born of God s promise, who are born according to the Spirit, being able to inherit God s promised good land Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Hagar symbolizing the covenant of law: Bringing forth children unto slavery according to the law of Mount Sinai.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Being born according to man s flesh, not according to God s grace.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Having no share in God s promised good land.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The covenant of God s promise confirmed with the covenant of circumcision: Circumcision signifying the putting off of the flesh by the cutting off of the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Circumcision on the eighth day after birth signifying the receiving of the dealing of the cross in resurrection.</S>
   </TEXT>
